16:24.454 --> 16:25.235
Moses is dead.

16:26.697 --> 16:28.240
Therefore, I love these words.

16:28.881 --> 16:30.644
The time has come.

16:33.067 --> 16:34.429
Maybe that's all you needed to hear today.

16:37.314 --> 16:39.397
The time has come.

16:40.759 --> 16:41.300
It's 2020.

16:41.441 --> 16:44.946
What have you been waiting for?

16:46.306 --> 16:47.628
to take your life to the next level.

16:49.431 --> 16:54.339
The time has come to change your life.

16:55.320 --> 17:10.223
Josh, Moses is dead, and now is the time for you to lead these people, the Israelites, across the Jordan River, into the land that I promised them to your forefather Abraham and Genesis chapter 15.

17:11.646 --> 17:14.450
The time has come.

17:14.850 --> 17:16.973
Not to set up camp in the wilderness.

17:18.115 --> 17:19.497
Not to start an NFL team.

17:19.638 --> 17:20.940
Not to start a baseball team.

17:20.960 --> 17:21.821
Not to start a business.

17:21.881 --> 17:22.242
No, no, no.

17:22.683 --> 17:23.604
Josh, listen up.

17:23.624 --> 17:24.205
Pay attention.

17:24.546 --> 17:25.086
Super clear.

17:25.848 --> 17:30.315
You're going to take my people across the Jordan River into the promised land.

17:30.355 --> 17:31.076
Did they have a target?

17:31.096 --> 17:31.517
Yes or no?

17:32.178 --> 17:32.899
Did they have a target?

17:32.919 --> 17:33.279
Yes or no?

17:33.320 --> 17:33.740
Talk to me.

17:33.941 --> 17:34.361
Yes or no?

17:34.381 --> 17:35.102
Did they have a target?

17:35.443 --> 17:36.965
Well, did they have extreme clarity?

17:37.186 --> 17:39.309
Did Joshua have a vision to chase after?

17:39.369 --> 17:39.890
Yes?

17:40.738 --> 17:43.042
He knew exactly what he was supposed to do.

17:43.302 --> 17:46.246
He was going to take these people across the Jordan River.

17:46.267 --> 17:46.507
Why?

17:46.747 --> 17:48.590
Because the time had come.

17:48.650 --> 17:49.391
Has your time come?

17:49.772 --> 17:50.453
Are you tired?

17:50.854 --> 17:51.675
Are you exhausted?

17:51.695 --> 17:54.459
Are you frustrated enough to say, God, I think it's time.

17:54.519 --> 17:57.083
It's time to change my life.

17:58.425 --> 17:59.287
Extreme clarity.

17:59.527 --> 18:02.772
Why does extreme clarity help people to get into the Promised Land?

18:02.932 --> 18:03.553
How does that work?

18:04.094 --> 18:06.738
Well, in your notes, extreme clarity produces focus.

18:07.842 --> 18:13.010
and focus is the most powerful thing a human being has within themselves, the ability to focus.

18:13.050 --> 18:19.699
Now most people don't focus, but when people do focus, they do amazing things with or without God.

18:22.323 --> 18:26.029
Lots of people are atheists, agnostics, want nothing to do with God and they've changed the world.

18:26.710 --> 18:26.890
Why?

18:27.070 --> 18:29.374
Because of this thing called focus.

18:29.794 --> 18:30.676
Think of Adolf Hitler.

18:33.059 --> 18:35.122
Successfully killed 11 million people.

18:36.482 --> 18:38.985
probably the epitome of evil embodied.

18:40.246 --> 18:40.987
How did he do that?

18:42.228 --> 18:50.316
He was completely and utterly focused on building his regime.

18:51.257 --> 18:51.698
Focus.

18:52.018 --> 18:52.839
It's powerful.

18:53.820 --> 18:54.881
This is how human beings do.

18:54.901 --> 18:56.583
This is how Mother Teresa changed the world.

18:56.803 --> 18:57.243
Focus.

18:58.004 --> 18:59.666
This is how Steve Jobs changed the world.

18:59.926 --> 19:00.426
Focus.

19:01.548 --> 19:03.890
This is how Bill Gates changed the world.

19:04.194 --> 19:06.337
He focused.

19:06.357 --> 19:07.738
You don't even need God for this.

19:07.758 --> 19:09.521
Can I say that in church and you guys be okay?

19:09.541 --> 19:10.121
Can I say that?

19:10.922 --> 19:12.084
I'm not talking.

19:12.104 --> 19:14.166
We need God.

19:14.307 --> 19:16.729
But this is just a thing that God has made us with.

19:16.750 --> 19:17.991
The ability to focus.

19:18.051 --> 19:23.378
And when a human being focuses, they can almost just do almost about anything.

19:24.599 --> 19:29.485
Kobe Bryant is a person that I respect even more so now that he's retired.

19:29.786 --> 19:31.688
He's one of the greatest players in the NBA.

19:31.948 --> 19:33.330
He was the greatest

19:33.602 --> 19:35.104
Laker of all time.

19:36.185 --> 19:41.851
Notice I didn't say player of all time, because he's not the greatest player of all time.

19:41.871 --> 19:43.973
But he is the greatest Laker of all time.

19:44.094 --> 19:45.675
He's got five championship rings.

19:46.977 --> 19:49.540
He actually has more 60-point games than Michael Jordan.

19:50.000 --> 19:52.243
That's about the only thing that he has over Michael.

19:52.283 --> 19:56.868
But anyway, much respect to Kobe, much respect to Kobe.

19:57.809 --> 19:59.491
In an interview recently, this is what he said.

20:00.732 --> 20:02.514
Basketball for me was the most important thing.

20:02.914 --> 20:07.180
When he was 13 years old, he decided he wanted to be the greatest of all time.

20:08.542 --> 20:09.804
It was the most important thing in his life.

20:10.144 --> 20:12.367
Complete extreme clarity.

20:12.788 --> 20:20.979
So everything I saw, whether it was TV shows, books I read, or people I talked to, watch this, everything was done to try to learn how to become a better basketball player.

20:21.720 --> 20:22.201
Everything.

20:22.381 --> 20:29.271
On the night he got drafted, when he was 18, went from high school to the NBA, instead of going out and having a party with his friends, guess where he went?

20:29.912 --> 20:31.474
He went to the gym to shoot jump shots.

20:32.802 --> 20:35.205
He was notoriously known for being on a recluse.

20:36.006 --> 20:43.355
After the games, his teammates would go out and have fun and have party where he would go home or he would stay late and shoot and practice or work on some skills.

20:45.498 --> 20:53.308
And he wasn't the tallest and he wasn't the fastest and he wasn't the quickest and he wasn't the strongest and he wasn't the biggest, but he was one of the best.

20:54.169 --> 20:58.434
He separated himself because he was completely and utterly focused.

20:58.454 --> 20:59.595
And where did that focus come from?

20:59.636 --> 21:01.618
It came from his clarity.

21:01.730 --> 21:02.732
of what He wanted.

21:02.752 --> 21:03.893
Is this making sense?

21:03.913 --> 21:04.294
Yes or no?

21:06.277 --> 21:14.469
See, what happens when we focus in is we leverage this thing that God has made us with called our reticular activating system, our RAS in your notes.

21:14.549 --> 21:16.813
We leverage our reticular activating system.

21:16.853 --> 21:21.160
It's this little piece of our brain that lies at the bottom of our brain stem.

21:21.180 --> 21:22.682
It's about the size of our pinky.

21:23.603 --> 21:25.426
And what it does is it serves as a filter.

21:26.082 --> 21:28.865
We have thousands and thousands of images coming at us every day.

21:28.966 --> 21:35.934
Every day colors people, languages, different videos, different ideas, and we can't possibly process it all.

21:35.974 --> 21:36.435
It's too much.

21:36.495 --> 21:37.116
It overwhelms us.

21:37.136 --> 21:45.466
So our RAS serves as our filter, and it only allows in information that we deem or that it deems relevant or important.

21:46.447 --> 21:47.609
This is how we get things done.

21:47.669 --> 21:53.837
Otherwise, we wouldn't get anything done because we'd be completely distracted and some of you are, which is why you don't get anything done.

21:54.257 --> 21:54.898
Anyway,

21:55.778 --> 21:58.782
Your RAS is God's tool to help you to focus.

21:58.822 --> 22:00.404
Now, how, but here's the question.

22:01.225 --> 22:06.071
What tells the RAS to let certain information in and block other information out?

22:06.251 --> 22:08.233
Well, that's your choice.

22:09.555 --> 22:10.736
What you choose to focus on.

22:11.678 --> 22:15.983
Whatever you choose to focus on will then allow information in that is pertinent to that idea.

22:16.023 --> 22:17.084
This is how it works.

22:17.545 --> 22:21.810
In your notes, there's a little triangle, it's a circle up here, but we first choose to focus in.

22:22.466 --> 22:23.427
Where'd the focus come from?

22:23.467 --> 22:24.589
It came from extreme clarity.

22:24.789 --> 22:26.953
Kobe Bryant wanted to be the best player in the world.

22:27.634 --> 22:28.595
So we start to focus.

22:28.675 --> 22:31.660
Then our brain only allows in information.

22:31.840 --> 22:36.086
Our RAS only allows in information relevant to what we're focusing on.

22:36.667 --> 22:38.851
You could also put the word evidence down here.

22:38.871 --> 22:44.359
It's searching for information and evidence to bring about this result that you chose to focus on.

22:45.240 --> 22:51.890
And then what happens is we begin to develop a belief system because now we have evidence and we believe it's possible to do that thing.

22:52.898 --> 22:55.561
I remember when I was in high school, I wanted to be the best basketball player.

22:55.581 --> 22:56.682
I wanted to be Michael Jordan.

22:56.882 --> 22:57.163
I did.

22:57.203 --> 23:02.809
Problem was I was 6'3", and not very athletic, and had a lot of problems, other problems too.

23:02.889 --> 23:05.191
But I wanted to be the next Michael Jordan.

23:05.992 --> 23:07.314
And so I would focus on that.

23:08.355 --> 23:09.336
And I would practice.

23:09.916 --> 23:14.601
And remember one particular game, I was coming down the left side, we were playing our rival, New York High School.

23:16.023 --> 23:22.610
And it was like five, four, three, two, we were down two points, and I hit this three pointer to win the game.

23:23.362 --> 23:51.698
at the buzzer, and the crowd came out, and I was a sophomore in high school, I was about 15 years old, and my teammates cleared the bench, and they started to, you know, gang tackle me, and so I'm like, on the ground like this, and everybody screaming, and the crowd's coming out, and if my brother hadn't come over to me, my older brother was on my team, he came over to me, and he straddled me like this, and he put his arms over me, and he basically held the whole team on his back, and the crowd, and they were all jumping and screaming,

23:52.066 --> 23:56.270
And if he hadn't done that, I probably would have died that day.

23:56.290 --> 23:58.232
So I owe my life to my older brother Jimmy.

23:59.673 --> 24:04.038
And after they started to come off of his back, he picked me up and he grabbed me and he dragged me into the locker room.

24:05.119 --> 24:10.784
And it was like this euphoric ESPN moment, like, nah, nah, nah, nah, it was the highlight of my life.

24:13.407 --> 24:21.074
And what happened was I was so focused, now I had information, now I had evidence that created a belief

24:22.338 --> 24:22.679
good.

24:23.580 --> 24:25.904
I hit a game winning buzzer beating shot.

24:27.166 --> 24:38.924
And then I took that belief system and I took it into my junior year and took it into my senior year and broke the scoring record at my high school and I wasn't a great basketball player but I was a good high school player.

24:38.964 --> 24:41.888
How did that happen?

24:42.369 --> 24:44.212
It happened because of the RAS.

24:45.134 --> 24:45.955
That's the way it works.

24:45.995 --> 24:48.018
That's how people achieve

24:48.610 --> 24:49.813
great things with their life.

24:49.873 --> 24:54.806
They choose to focus, and then their brain gathers information and evidence which generates belief.

24:54.826 --> 24:56.289
Now, this works the opposite way, too.

24:56.971 --> 24:57.773
This kills people.

24:58.515 --> 24:59.498
This destroys people.

24:59.878 --> 25:02.866
People focus on, well, I'm not good enough.

25:02.978 --> 25:04.240
I'll never lose the weight.

25:04.700 --> 25:07.223
I can't run a business or I'm not a very good parent.

25:07.403 --> 25:11.949
And then we gather up information that supports that what you're focusing on.

25:11.969 --> 25:15.674
See, see, look, you failed as a mom, as a business person.

25:15.694 --> 25:17.816
Now there's evidence and it generates a belief.

25:18.237 --> 25:20.039
Oh man, I knew I couldn't do this.

25:20.239 --> 25:21.341
I knew I couldn't run a business.

25:21.361 --> 25:22.482
I knew I couldn't be a good mom.

25:22.502 --> 25:23.043
I knew I couldn't.

25:23.223 --> 25:24.244
I knew I couldn't be a good student.

25:24.505 --> 25:27.428
And then it just round and round we go.

25:28.149 --> 25:29.531
This works for good or for bad.

25:31.293 --> 25:32.114
It's your choice.

25:33.378 --> 25:35.260
Where does the focus come from?

25:35.460 --> 25:36.902
It comes from extreme clarity.

25:37.343 --> 25:38.103
Caesar Milan.

25:38.584 --> 25:39.765
I got to tell this story.

25:40.086 --> 25:42.929
The dog whisper came to this country with $100.

25:45.712 --> 25:47.474
Became the greatest dog trainer of all time.

25:47.554 --> 25:53.581
Do you know he trains governors and presidents in different countries how to deal with their dogs?

25:54.502 --> 25:55.263
Who does that?

25:55.564 --> 25:56.585
Caesar Milan does.

25:56.625 --> 25:57.586
The dog whisper.

25:58.146 --> 26:01.550
When he was 13, when he was 13, he asked his mom.

26:02.031 --> 26:04.334
It really was a question, but it was a desire in his heart.

26:04.354 --> 26:07.838
Mom, do you think I can become the greatest dog trainer in the world?

26:08.059 --> 26:11.043
And his mom responded and said, honey, you can do whatever you focus on.

26:11.323 --> 26:20.555
When he was asked how he had such incredible success coming from Mexico to America with $100 in his pocket, how he became the greatest dog trainer in the world.

26:20.575 --> 26:21.376
You know what his answer was?

26:21.897 --> 26:22.698
I focused.

26:23.699 --> 26:26.162
My entire life was focused on my goal.

26:28.130 --> 26:29.573
So how do you and I do that?

26:29.774 --> 26:32.720
How do you and I gain this extreme clarity?

26:32.760 --> 26:34.103
Let me give you three quick ideas.

26:35.025 --> 26:35.847
This is how I do it.

26:36.408 --> 26:40.156
Number one, you have to spend time in God's word every single day.

26:40.958 --> 26:42.802
Put God's truth.

26:43.522 --> 26:45.905
in front of your mind every single day.

26:45.945 --> 26:48.007
This is what he says is most important.

26:48.248 --> 26:50.611
Listen, this isn't a self-help program.

26:50.831 --> 26:52.633
This isn't a motivational speech.

26:52.993 --> 26:56.017
Like Joshua didn't sit back and say, you know, what do I want to do with my life?

26:56.077 --> 26:58.360
It's 2020, you know, or whatever year it was.

26:59.882 --> 27:00.903
What do I want to do with my life?

27:00.943 --> 27:07.551
I think I'd like to take the people across the Jordan River into the promise.

27:07.691 --> 27:08.913
It wasn't Joshua's idea.

27:09.013 --> 27:10.034
Whose idea was it?

27:10.562 --> 27:13.490
It was God's idea, hey, Josh, my servant Moses is dead.

27:14.352 --> 27:15.034
Now is the time.

27:16.157 --> 27:17.601
You've been wandering around for 40 years.

27:18.102 --> 27:20.990
Take my people across the Jordan into the promised land.

27:21.532 --> 27:24.680
We are searching for what God has for our life.

27:24.740 --> 27:26.866
God, what does my promised land look like?

27:27.298 --> 27:29.221
What does mind upgrade look like?

27:29.241 --> 27:30.783
Well, you gotta get into his word.

27:30.803 --> 27:33.087
Listen to what it says in Romans chapter 12.

27:33.147 --> 27:38.696
Don't copy the behavior and customs of this world, but let God transform you into a new person by changing the way you think.

27:38.916 --> 27:40.819
And then when you change the way you think, watch this.

27:41.560 --> 27:44.785
Then you will learn to know God's will for your life.

27:44.805 --> 27:46.408
So I don't know what God wants from my life.

27:46.468 --> 27:48.250
I don't know what his will is for my life.

27:48.270 --> 27:51.676
Well, it's because you're not spending time in this book every single day.

27:51.936 --> 27:53.138
He will reveal it to you.

27:53.602 --> 27:58.589
what his will is for relationships, your sexuality, your finances, for your occupation.

27:58.869 --> 28:03.255
He will show you his will if you spend time in his book.

28:03.335 --> 28:04.717
Rick Warren said it famously.

28:04.777 --> 28:10.826
He said, daily reading of God's word keeps you within God's voice, range of God's voice.

28:10.846 --> 28:14.331
This is some of the best advice I took maybe 15 years ago.

28:14.591 --> 28:17.034
And every single day I expose myself to God's word.

28:17.074 --> 28:17.195
Why?

28:17.215 --> 28:18.256
Because he speaks to us.

28:18.737 --> 28:22.642
He speaks to us about what he wants our life to look like.

28:23.010 --> 28:24.652
spend daily time in God's word.

28:24.872 --> 28:30.339
Number two, meditate, meditate on the brevity of life, the shortness of life.

28:30.899 --> 28:40.871
Life is short, a very dear friend of mine, and a dear friend of all of you, if you knew who he was, and some of you do, passed away on Christmas day this year, Don Byers.

28:41.572 --> 28:43.915
He probably rocked your babies here at church.

28:43.955 --> 28:45.677
He served on the impact team and the nursery.

28:46.057 --> 28:47.139
Precious, precious man.

28:47.479 --> 28:50.002
I did his funeral just recently.

28:51.618 --> 28:52.800
He lived a very good life.

28:53.421 --> 28:54.562
He blessed many, many people.

28:55.744 --> 28:57.166
But here's what I took away from that funeral.

28:58.488 --> 28:59.449
Man, life is short.

29:00.691 --> 29:07.221
Don was here, enjoying life, being a great-granddad, and now Don is not here.

29:08.262 --> 29:15.152
The Bible talks about life being like a vapor or a mist or like the flowers of the field that's here today, and then they're gone tomorrow.

29:15.312 --> 29:16.134
We don't have forever.

29:17.776 --> 29:19.218
Life is short.

29:19.330 --> 29:23.275
And when we think about the brevity of life and the shortness of life, what happens?

29:23.836 --> 29:27.360
Well, what happens is the most important things begin to rise to the surface.

29:28.041 --> 29:30.144
And the less important things fade away.

29:30.885 --> 29:34.089
The shortness of life gives us wisdom when we think about it.

29:34.309 --> 29:36.271
Listen to the psalmist in Psalm 90 verse 12.

29:36.552 --> 29:40.857
Teach us to realize the brevity of life so that we may gain a heart of what?

29:41.578 --> 29:41.978
Wisdom.

29:42.119 --> 29:42.699
What is wisdom?

29:42.759 --> 29:44.922
It's knowing what to do and when to do it.

29:44.942 --> 29:47.986
It's knowing what's most important in life.

29:49.314 --> 29:50.515
What's really going on?

29:52.017 --> 29:55.782
There's a Twitter handle called the Daily Death Reminder.

29:56.263 --> 29:56.863
It's kind of dark.

30:00.868 --> 30:02.330
I want to show you what it says here.

30:02.751 --> 30:04.152
The Daily Death Reminder.

30:04.192 --> 30:05.254
Some of you are going to follow it.

30:05.274 --> 30:06.676
Some of you are like, I won't follow that.

30:06.696 --> 30:07.296
Are you crazy?

30:08.197 --> 30:10.961
The Daily Death Reminder.

30:12.142 --> 30:16.548
They follow no one, but they have 23,900 followers.

30:17.669 --> 30:18.290
I'm one of them.

30:18.882 --> 30:21.645
They send out one tweet a day, whoever this person is.

30:21.665 --> 30:22.446
You know what the tweet is?

30:23.087 --> 30:23.968
It's a real simple tweet.

30:23.988 --> 30:25.610
Same tweet every single day.

30:26.652 --> 30:27.933
You will die someday.

30:28.794 --> 30:29.335
That's the tweet.

30:30.236 --> 30:31.398
Every day, same tweet.

30:32.058 --> 30:38.406
And every day it is favorited anywhere from 550 to 800 times and it's retweeted anywhere from 150 to 200 times.

30:39.027 --> 30:41.210
I like them and I retweet them sometimes so you see that.

30:42.191 --> 30:43.593
You say, why would you follow that?

30:44.053 --> 30:44.594
Why would you?

30:45.538 --> 30:48.422
That's dark, I know, I confess, I'm a bit dark.

30:48.442 --> 30:50.264
Okay, as your pastor, I have a dark side, okay?

30:50.284 --> 30:56.311
So, here's why I follow that, because I need to be reminded that life is short.

30:56.652 --> 30:58.113
Like, I'm gonna die, you're gonna die.

30:58.374 --> 31:03.240
And if that's true, and it is true, then I need to be about the most important thing.

31:04.141 --> 31:09.928
Meditating and contemplating the brevity of life gives you extreme clarity about what's most important.

31:09.968 --> 31:10.389
Yes or no?

31:10.789 --> 31:11.230
Yes or no?

31:11.410 --> 31:12.091
Okay, okay.

31:12.111 --> 31:14.834
So, number two, think about the brevity

31:15.074 --> 31:18.317
of life, let me give you this third one, number three, in your notes.

31:19.438 --> 31:21.540
Ask this question, does it impact others?

31:22.421 --> 31:27.706
There are seven and a half billion people on this planet, there's no way your upgrade will touch, will just be for you.

31:28.146 --> 31:29.448
It's going to touch other people.

31:30.949 --> 31:33.531
It's not gonna be just for you.

31:33.672 --> 31:44.722
Philippians chapter two, verse four, the apostle Paul says this, let each of you look not only to your own interests, don't just think about yourself this year, just don't think about yourself this decade, but also take a,

31:44.866 --> 31:47.649
Take an interest and stay with me and others.

31:48.230 --> 31:51.653
Your upgrade will touch the lives of others.

31:53.515 --> 31:55.397
Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. got this.

31:55.417 --> 31:56.078
He understood this.

31:56.138 --> 31:58.120
He gave his life for the benefit of others.

31:58.160 --> 31:59.041
Listen to what he said.

32:00.342 --> 32:03.145
Life's most persistent and urgent question is this.

32:03.386 --> 32:05.768
What are you doing for others?

32:07.510 --> 32:11.474
If your upgrade does not touch the lives of others, it's probably not from God.

32:11.842 --> 32:14.327
There's seven and a half billion of us on this planet.

32:14.467 --> 32:19.537
It's going, your upgrade is going to be for you, yes, but it's also going to be for others.

32:22.283 --> 32:30.078
